                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Heya,
<br />

<br />
I've had a chance to glance over the possible aa's for the OOW expansion, and while I know that they are not final as of yet, I am disappointed that the /pet hold command aa has once again been kept from enchanters.  Most other classes are getting even further pet commands, and we still lack this very useful one.  As has been stated in numerous other thread, our animations continue to be sorely lacking.  Many of us wouldn't mind pet focus items to be useful for our class as well.
<br />

<br />
Is there a particular reason for this?  Are we being passed over for any real pet abilities due to the fact that we can charm?  I love charming, solo or grouping, but there are situations where, for whatever reason, our animation is the only option.  Also, due to bad pet control problems, my guild instituted a no pets w/o pet hold rule on all raids.  Does /pet hold have some innate ability in it that could somehow be misused while charming?  Or are enchanter animations just never going to get any love?
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I don't want to ramble on.  Please, all I am asking is that someone give us some kind of clue as to why we are always passed over in this regard, even though we are obviously a pet class?
<br />

<br />
Thanks,</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: violet">Sage Loriwen Tathrenlin</span></span>
