Your guess on the controllable pets is prolly correct... however, I have always been an independent type of chanter and mostly soloed till 52. Partly, because at first I didn´t know there was a LFG tool to begign with, LOL. I would enter a zone, OOC LFG and solo, or just feel like solo all together and don´t even OOC anything. And let me tell you something, without my pet, I would not have made it pass level 12. 
<br />

<br />
Even when grouping, pet would smack back after I got a mez resisted and a couple slaps from mob and steal agro from me, allowing me for much safer mezzing on resists. Pet was my AC and my HPs. 
<br />

<br />
Before PoP there were 2 types of chanters, the ones using pets, who will die much much less, and the ones who didn´t who would get lots of rezzes on mez resists. They could AE stun, yes, but so could I on top of my pet. 
<br />

<br />
After PoP none of the mobs would fall for pet bait, so it really became useless (using the same ol'Dazzle as before, funny how that worked). Due to its uselesness, I understand where you are coming from when you say it is just for flavor. However, I could make a case saying in today's game, mez and charm are just for flavor just the same. So what is our core class skill now? Buff bot?
<br />

<br />
What really pisses me off on this issue is not only SoE nerfed charm and provided 99.99% of content single pullable, specially in GoD and WoS, they didn´t even bothered to place DC pets on OOW or GoD expansions, not to mention a much needed upgrade DC level to maybe 55?
