                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well.. Raid size depends on the DPS needed for that event. The main idea is MAX damage as possible. This varies due to available people  logged in for the Raid, but the list starts at wizard and goes down from there. I would say enchanter is not on the DPS list, so NO DOTS are allowed if you are not assigned as DPS.
<br />

<br />
Max RAID Size is about 72, but sometimes a Second RAID party is allowed for more utility and extra flags. The second raid will do things like MGB buffs and Rez or Kite adds. Engaging the Raid BOSS is not allowed for the second raid party. Keep in mind the second raid is there because the first Raid is FULL (72). So,... Yes all available slots will be used for DOT classes. Some of the available slots are taken as debuffs (resist lower, slow, cripple). Wasting more slots with our dismal dots would really hinder the raid. Pets don't count as DOTS due to lack of pet hold in our class, we can't use them on ANY Raids.
<br />

<br />
Imagine all available Boss slots filled with Enchanter dots that stack. Wouldn't that be a HOOT... failed due to timeout. That's like attacking the broodmother in the Great Divide while solo and melee with a rusty weapon. "Her hitpoints keep going up??" Maybe I should find another wurm to play with. <img src="images/smiles/icon_butt.gif" alt="icon_butt.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="images/smiles/eusa_drool.gif" alt="eusa_drool.gif" border="0" /> <span style="color: violet"></span></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Chicks Rule, Boys Drool <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /></td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
