                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I hardly ever use the animation anymore due largely to the lack of a /pet hold.  I agree that I think they withheld it because the pets are not controllable.  On raids I never use it.  We are doing SSRA stuff right now and the cursed cycle for example has a lot of AoE mobs so Shiny Bob would just goo Kamikaze the big boss mob the first time the AoE went off.
<br />
Even those of us with pet hold have to kill our pets when it's called because of someone else who didn't have it let their pet wander (another mage in guild didn't have it yet).
<br />
Even if we're just farming key pieces there I generally just slap on NDT and go to town with my Delightful Orb rather than summon the animation.
<br />
If there's any chance I will be charming for CC (a rarity I know) I won't summon the pet.
<br />
The only time I will use it is if I'm in a boring single pull group like in WoS where charming is out of the question and I know the pet won't cause undue mischief if it decides to act up.
<br />
If we had a /pet hold I could see myself using it more though.  I'd kinda like to have it but I'm also rather ambivalent because it's pretty weak as far as DPS goes.  As for peeling aggro it just won't happen after a tash and/or slow/mez resist so I just rely on rune/stun/root/mez to get me out of trouble.  I can't really use it to tank for me either because of it's lack of hps, again I just NDT up and rune tank myself.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=788008" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jeradim</a> - 67 Mage on Bertoxx/<a href="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=143285101" target="_blank" class="postlink">22 Conjuror/20 Alchemist on Guk</a>
